summary:
This is a natural style ENB with strong atmosphere around you when you play
Based on NLA Weather
descriptionHtml:
[url=http://s700.photobucket.com/user/macho_k/media/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/VANILLAICECREAMENB.png.html][img]http://i700.photobucket.com/albums/ww8/macho_k/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/VANILLAICECREAMENB.png[/img][/url]

[size=4][b]
DESCRIPTION[/b][/size]
This is a ENB preset intended for use with NLA Weather and ELFX for lighting
while the visual is different with original NLA but i tried my best to keep the natural and atmospherics feel strong to your gameplay
If you like to take screenshots, upload them here. I love to see them :D
I hope you're gonna like it, Enjoy




[size=4][b]
[url=http://s700.photobucket.com/user/macho_k/media/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/InstallationTITLE.png.html][img]http://i700.photobucket.com/albums/ww8/macho_k/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/InstallationTITLE.png[/img][/url]

LETS GET STARTED[/b][/size]
Vanilla Ice Cream ENB Installation Video from [url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Ca25g9e04cM] CHABAL [/url] and [url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=86MGf1rLGvk] Heisennburgg [/url] (old version)

1. Copy this ENB file to your Skyrim directory
2. Download Latest ENBseries, copy the d3d9.dll and enbhost.exe from "WrapperVersion" to your skyrim directory
    Latest ENBseries files can be found[url=http://enbdev.com/mod_tesskyrim_v0319.htm] here [/url]
3. Install Vanilla Ice Cream Data Folder
4. Editing SkyrimPrefs.ini:
    fGamma=1.0000
    bFloatPointRenderTarget=1
    bDeferredShadows=1
    bTreesReceiveShadows=1
    bDrawLandShadows=1
    bShadowsOnGrass=1
5. Make sure to disable Antialiasing and Anisotropic Filtering in your
    graphics card's Control Panel


[url=http://s700.photobucket.com/user/macho_k/media/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/RequiredTITLE.png.html][img]http://i700.photobucket.com/albums/ww8/macho_k/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/RequiredTITLE.png[/img][/url]
[size=4][b]
REQUIREMENTS MOD[/b][/size]

1. [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/50065/?] Natural Lighting and Atmospherics for ENB by Confidence-Man [/url]
    need only esp file (Place the Natural Lighting and Atmospherics.esp file in the data folder)
    [color=#e69138]--> Use NLA 1.4 Version[/color]
2. [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/27043/?] Enhanced Lights and FX by anamorfus [/url]
    [color=#ff7700][color=#ffffff]--> Install Main CORE Files and Optional ELFX Enhancer (EnhancedLightsandFX.esp and ELFXEnhancer.esp)[/color][/color]
3. [url=http://enbseries.enbdev.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=1499] Mindflux's Skyrim Particle Patch [/url]
    install Skyrim Particle Patch for ENB-All-In-One and Skyrim Subsurface Scattering Patch for ENB
4. [url=http://enbdev.com/enbseries/forum/viewtopic.php?f=6&t=1930&p=57538&sid=40a110d0b14c8dd4daf7aa65e7990ff8&sid=40a110d0b14c8dd4daf7aa65e7990ff8#p57538] --JawZ-- optimized Skymesh [/url]
    Place the atmosphere.nif file in the sky folder (Skyrim\Data\meshes\sky)
    [color=#e69138]--> Just simply create new folder and name it sky if the sky folder isn't there[/color]
[size=4][b]

[url=http://s700.photobucket.com/user/macho_k/media/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/RecommendedTITLE.png.html][img]http://i700.photobucket.com/albums/ww8/macho_k/Forum/SKYRIM%20SS/RecommendedTITLE.png[/img][/url]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/61995/?] Tamriel Reloaded HD by 32cm [/url] i don't think you need anything else below if you choose to install this
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/49661/?] 4K Parallax Skyrim by Pfuscher aka Zerwas1 by Pfuscher aka Zerwas1 [/url]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/141/?] Skyrim Flora Overhaul by vurt[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/66971/?]Dark Fantasy Overhaul by AceeQ[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/66750/?]Skyrim Spring Overhaul by AceeQ[/url]

[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/55240/?] Remove Underwater Grass and other stuff too - A Performance Mod by Cauug [/url] choose small rock remover
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/6387/?] Skyrim Performance PLUS by VirusType2 aka Vergis [/url] i always use this if i have performance issue in few areas

You still need to use [url=https://loot.github.io/] LOOT [/url]and[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/25859/?] TES5Edit by ElminsterAU [/url] to stable modded game



[size=4][b]
COMPABILITY[/b][/size]

This is a ENB preset intended for use with NLA and ELFX so using other weather or lighting mods will result looking weird in your game however you can use [url=http://enbdev.com/enbseries/forum/viewtopic.php?f=6&t=1930&sid=3f9f9d83f59140a735eaadf8972d51a0] Enhanced Lighting for ENB/ELE by --JawZ--[/url] or [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/17609/?] Relighting Skyrim by NovakDalton and --JawZ--[/url] for Interior lighting if you want, i think it's compatible
[color=#ff7700]-not compatible with Climates Of Tamriel, Pure Weathers or any other weather mods.
-not compatible with RLO
-not compatible with imaginator

[/color][size=4][b]
